Frequently Asked Questions for SLM Corporation (NASDAQ:SLM)
What is SLM Corporation's stock symbol?

SLM Corporation trades on the NASDAQ under the ticker symbol "SLM."



How were SLM Corporation's earnings last quarter?

SLM Corporation (NASDAQ:SLM) released its quarterly earnings data on Wednesday, July, 19th. The company reported $0.16 earnings per share for the quarter, meeting the Thomson Reuters' consensus estimate of $0.16. The firm had revenue of $269.89 million for the quarter, compared to analyst estimates of $268.69 million. SLM Corporation had a net margin of 22.81% and a return on equity of 16.31%. The company's revenue for the quarter was up 26.8% compared to the same quarter last year. During the same quarter in the prior year, the business earned $0.12 EPS.  View SLM Corporation's Earnings History.



When will SLM Corporation make its next earnings announcement?

SLM Corporation is scheduled to release their next quarterly earnings announcement on Tuesday, October, 17th 2017. View Earnings Estimates for SLM Corporation.



What guidance has SLM Corporation issued on next quarter's earnings?

SLM Corporation updated its FY17 earnings guidance on Wednesday, July, 19th. The company provided earnings per share (EPS) guidance of $0.71-0.72 for the period, compared to the Thomson Reuters consensus EPS estimate of $0.72. 



Where is SLM Corporation's stock going? Where will SLM Corporation's stock price be in 2017?

8 equities research analysts have issued 12-month target prices for SLM Corporation's shares. Their predictions range from $8.50 to $15.00. On average, they anticipate SLM Corporation's stock price to reach $12.44 in the next year. View Analyst Ratings for SLM Corporation.



What are analysts saying about SLM Corporation stock?

Here are some recent quotes from research analysts about SLM Corporation stock: 
1. According to Zacks Investment Research, "Sallie Mae’s shares significantly outperformed the Zacks categorized Consumer Loan industry over the last six months. Further, estimates have remained stable ahead of the company’s Q2 earnings release. Also, the company has positive earnings surprises in recent quarters.The company is focused on strengthening its Private Education Loan assets and revenues, maintaining a strong capital position and introducing multiple complementary new products. The economic recovery and declining unemployment rate should help Sallie Mae maintain its leading position in the student lending market. Further, Sallie Mae’s profitability is likely to be supported by recently approved Financial Choice Act. However, a competitive business environment and escalating expenses remain near-term concerns. Further, Sallie Mae faces concentration risk due to over dependence on brokered deposits." (7/17/2017)
2. Wedbush analysts commented, "We are initiating coverage on SLM Corp. (SLM) with an OUTPERFORM rating and a $13 price target. SLM is the largest private student loan originator in the country, accounting for over 50% of private originations. Over the last three years, growth in private student loan balances has been significant, loan quality stable, and adjusted EPS increased at an annualized rate of 20%. We think these trends will continue over the next three to five years." (1/30/2017)
3. Jefferies Group LLC analysts commented, "SLM reported 4Q16 EPS of $0.15, beating both our estimate and consensus of $0.14. We classify 4Q16 as another solid quarter with strong fundamentals including continued strong top-line growth, consistent credit and strong expense controls. Preliminary 2017 guidance implies 28% growth at the midpoint which is in-line consensus and reflects strong secular growth. We consider the growth factors very appealing and continue to favor SLM. Results versus our model. Net interest income of $245M beat our forecast of $237M while non-interest income of $9M was slightly lower than our $12M forecast. The provision for loan losses of $43M exceeded our $40M estimate somewhat offsetting the top-line beat although we note that credit remains very stable (i.e. NCOs were down meaningfully from year ago results). In addition, non-interest expense of $98M was slightly better than our estimate of $99M and produced an efficiency ratio of 38.5% versus our 40% forecast." (1/19/2017)
4. Barclays PLC analysts commented, "We hosted two days of investor meetings with SLM. Overall, we came away with a reinforced view on the long-term growth prospects of the stock. If anything, we are probably more bullish now. Prior to the election, SLM was already a robust growth story, but had some warranted legislative risks. Now those risks, at a minimum, are off the table in our view. And instead, we think the legislative/regulatory landscape has become more supportive to private student lending and could actually create catalysts. SLM could benefit from any one or a combination of potential catalysts that include, lower corporate taxes, reduction in Federal student lending, and a much less likely revival of the FFELP program in some form. While the stock has rallied +34% (vs. +2% SPX) since 11/9, SLM trades at ~14x 2017 EPS, and still at a discount to the broader SMIDcap bank group (~17x) and also a discount to our DCF- driven PT of $12 (up from $11, reflecting a lower discount rate). Ultimately, we think that none of these catalysts are fully priced in, so owning SLM here provides a free call option on EPS upside from these potential catalysts, in our view." (11/21/2016)




Who are some of SLM Corporation's key competitors?

 Some companies that are related to SLM Corporation include SVB Financial Group (SIVB), Iron Mountain Incorporated (IRM), Torchmark Corporation (TMK), Ageas SA (AGESY), KKR & Co. L.P. (KKR), SEI Investments Company (SEIC), Zions Bancorporation (ZION), American Financial Group (AFG), Bankinter SA (BKNIY), Reinsurance Group of America, Incorporated (RGA), W.R. Berkley Corporation (WRB), British Land Company PLC Sponsored ADR (BTLCY), Macerich Company (The) (MAC), Aercap Holdings N.V. (AER), East West Bancorp (EWBC), VEREIT (VER), Kimco Realty Corporation (KIM) and Scor SE (SCRYY).



